Citation.sTitle: Isothermal binary vapour liquid equilibrium for butanes and butenes with dimethylsulphide
Citation.sAbstract: Isothermal vapour liquid equilibrium was measured for dimethylsulphide + 1-butene (312.58 K), dimethylsulphide + cis-2-butene (312.59 K),  dimethylsulphide + trans-2-butene (317.30 K), dimethylsulphide + 2-methylpropene (312.60 K), dimethylsulphide + n-butane (317.41 K) and  dimethylsulphide + 2-methylpropane (307.86 K) with the static total pressure method. The experimental data were correlated with Legendrepolynomial  and the Wilson activity coefficient models. All six binary systems exhibited positive deviation from Raoult s law.
